    "While she was dean, she was also appointed to several boards and honors including fellowship to the American Academy of Arts and Sciences (2001-), Board of Managers, Swarthmore College (1987-1999), the Board of Directors of the and the board of the Alfred P. Sloan Foundation (2008-2020).": [],
    "In 2009, she was appointed vice-chair to former President Barack Obama\u2019s President\u2019s Committee on the Arts and the Humanities.": [],
    "Over the course of her tenure, the application pool to the Tisch School had become both larger and more academically selective, the diversity of faculty increased tenfold, and over three times the number of minority students were admitted before she retired in 2013.": [
