    "Campbell served as president of the historically black Spelman College from 2015-2022.": [],
    "Under her leadership, she built the first new academic facility for the college in 20 years, succeeded in a capital campaign fund to raise $250 million, increased the endowment fund to nearly $500 million, and expanded Spelman initiatives to interact with Atlanta Public Schools.": [],
    "In 2017, she was appointed to the Mayoral Advisory Commission on City Art, Monuments and Markers in New York City.": [],
    "Her book, <i>An American Odyssey: The Life and Work of Romare Bearden,</i> won the 2018 Hooks National Book Award from the Benjamin L. Hooks Institute for Social Change at the University of Memphis and was a finalist for the the 2019 Museum of African American History Stone Book Award; for this book, she was also a finalist for the 55th Georgia Author of the Year Award.": [
